<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Words Worth 50+ Points in Scrabble</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">Word of the Day · Scrabble Words Finder · English Solver</p>

<div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
  <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
  <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-600"></span>
  <span>6 min read</span>
</div>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">Most Scrabble turns score 15-30 points. But the game rewards bold plays — a single monster turn can swing the entire match. Scoring 50+ points in one play isn't luck; it's knowing which words hit premium squares hardest, when to hold tiles for a bingo, and how to exploit the board's geometry. Here's how the highest-scoring plays are built.</p>

<div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
  <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Record</div>
  <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">CAZIQUES — 392 pts</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">Highest verified single-word score in competitive play</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Played across two triple-word squares (triple-triple). CAZIQUES means "native chiefs of the West Indies" — and it earned Karl Khoshnaw a place in Scrabble history.</p>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Bingo Bonus: Instant 50+ Points</h2>

<p>The most reliable path to 50+ points is the bingo: play all 7 tiles and earn a 50-point bonus on top of the word's natural score. Since most 7-letter words score 12-20 base points, bingos typically land between 62-120+ points.</p>

