<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Triple-Triple: Scrabble's Ultimate Play</h2>

<p>A triple-triple occurs when a single word covers TWO triple-word squares. The word score is multiplied by 3, then by 3 again — a x9 multiplier. These plays are rare (maybe once every 50 games) but game-defining when they happen.</p>

